	abstract = {Although it does not have a very positive and desirable meaning as a word, when the word 'artificial' is used to qualify 'intelligence, ' it refers to a period that is the last known leg of development and technological revolution. This period describes the time when the concept of artificial intelligence, which states can use in every known field, can control many aspects of life. The period of artificial intelligence, which is the last of these periods, which changes in very short phases with the speed of technological developments, forms the basis of a higher period that humankind will pass through, perhaps in a few decades. It is also accepted that studies on artificial intelligence applications are in parallel with the level of development of countries in terms of becoming an information society and that the achievements in this field are reflected in public institutions and the quality of people's lives. As a pioneer in artificial intelligence, the United States' decades-long leadership in artificial intelligence (AI) research and development has brought cutting-edge, transformative technologies that improve lives, develop innovative industries, empower organizations and workers, and enhance national security. It can be argued that the US' aim in developing these technologies is to create a control mechanism in line with US values and interests and to maintain its long-standing 'leadership' status. Turkiye, which has prepared the National Artificial Intelligence Strategy roadmap with the aim of becoming a pioneer in s-government applications and becoming a country that produces technology, not just consumes it, has assigned an important mission to the Digital Transformation Office established under the Presidency with the Presidential Government System. For Turkiye, which still has a long way to go in terms of digitalization and artificial intelligence, prioritizing the concept of digital leadership and establishing the Department of Artificial Intelligence and other departments within the Digital Transformation Office are important steps to be at the forefront of the artificial intelligence world. This study aims to make a comparative analysis of the path taken by the USA, which is a pioneer in artificial intelligence studies, in public administration with the s-government approach, and the path taken by Turkiye, which has taken domestic and national steps in information technology, in the field of public administration within the scope of sgovernment approach. Additionally, it seeks to provide suggestions to improve the use of artificial intelligence to become an s-governmentleading country. © 2025 Nova Science Publishers, Inc. All rights reserved.},
