	abstract = {Abstract – The rapid emergence of Artificial Intelligence (AI) as a pivotal technology in the financial sector has generated increasing interest in its potential to advance economic and environmental sustainability. This research utilizes a systematic literature review (SLR) approach to analyze 40 articles from reputable scientific journals in the fields of economics and finance, using the Elton Bryson Stephens Company (EBSCO) database, which is known for its reliability in these areas. The primary aim is to assess emerging trends, pinpoint gaps and delve into the challenges associated with the implementation and utilization of AI within the realm of sustainable finance (SF). By delivering a methodical overview of the current literature, this study presents the first comprehensive review dedicated to the intersection of AI and SF. The findings indicate that, despite the potential for AI to revolutionize SF, there are significant hurdles to overcome, particularly concerning regulatory compliance, ethical considerations and the integration of AI-driven decision-making systems. © 2025 Elvira Anna Graziano, Gerardo Petroccione and Dario Siggia},
