	abstract = {The study underscores the critical role of healthcare logistics (HL), particularly in crises like the COVID-19 pandemic, where an efficient supply of life-saving drugs and instruments is imperative. Leveraging the Value-based Adoption Model (VAM) and Technology Organization Environment (TOE) model. We collected data from 460 healthcare professionals and analysed them using smartPLS 4.0 software, revealing that AI’s usefulness, cost-effectiveness, and relative advantage significantly influence the perceived value of HL. Conversely, perceived fees, technical challenges, and privacy risks significantly negatively impact perceived value. The study concludes that perceived value positively influences AI adoption, with the moderating effects of perceived industry pressure and financial readiness being notably positive and significant. Overall, this research offers valuable insights into the factors influencing AI adoption decisions in healthcare organisations, presenting a conceptual model that addresses both the benefits and challenges of the adoption process. © 2025 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.},
